# AI Development Rules (Cursor)

When generating frontend code:

1. Follow the **folder structure** (pages, components, hooks)
2. Place components in the **correct page folder**
3. Create **separate CSS files** per component
4. Use **Tailwind** for responsiveness
5. Use **BEM-style** class naming (`home-hero__title`, not `.title`)
6. Do **not** mix components from different pages
7. Prefer path aliases (`@/components/...`) when configured
8. Avoid inline styles except for truly dynamic values
9. Use hooks only when needed (interactive UI or data fetching)
10. When fetching data: include **loading** and **error** state

## Anti-Patterns to Avoid

| ❌ Don't | ✅ Do |
|----------|-------|
| One 500-line component | Split into < 150 line components |
| Generic `.container`, `.title` | `home-hero__container`, `about-team__title` |
| Mix page components | Keep `components/Home/` and `components/About/` separate |
| No error handling for fetch | Use loading/error state; wrap in ErrorBoundary |
| `any` in TypeScript | Define proper interfaces |
| Missing alt or semantic HTML | Check accessibility basics |
